<h1>Block or delete a user</h1>
<p>To block or delete a user go to the user&#8217;s account in system management, and choose <em>delete</em> or <em>block</em>.</p>
<h2>Blocked users</h2>
<p>Blocked users are intended for temporarily removing access privileges to the system.</p>
<p>You can unblock an account by going to the <em>Users</em> list in systems management and choose <em>Blocked</em> to show all blocked users. Choose the user you wish to undelete from the list and choose <em>Unblock</em> from the right hand panel.</p>
<h2>Deleted users</h2>
<p>Information about deleted users is kept by the system to maintain historical information.</p>
<p>You can undelete an account by going to the <em>Users</em> list in systems management and choose <em>Deleted</em> to show all deleted users. Choose the user you wish to undelete from the list and choose <em>Undelete</em> from the right hand panel.</p>
</div>

